{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:romans.3",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "romans",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Romans 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Romans 3 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:1",
      "text": "What advantage then hath the Jew: or what is the profit of circumcision?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:2",
      "text": "Much every way. First indeed, because the words of God were committed to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:3",
      "text": "For what if some of them have not believed? Shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect? God forbid!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:4",
      "text": "But God is true and every man a liar, as it is written: That thou mayest be justified in thy words and mayest overcome when thou art judged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:5",
      "text": "But if our injustice commend the justice of God, what shall we say? Is God unjust, who executeth wrath?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:6",
      "text": "(I speak according to man.) God forbid! Otherwise how shall God judge this world?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:7",
      "text": "For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie, unto his glory, why am I also yet judged as a sinner?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:8",
      "text": "And not rather (as we are slandered and as some affirm that we say) let us do evil that there may come good? Whose damnation is just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:9",
      "text": "What then? Do we excel them? No, not so. For we have charged both Jews and Greeks, that they are all under sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:10",
      "text": "As it is written: There is not any man just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:11",
      "text": "There is none that understandeth: there is none that seeketh after God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:12",
      "text": "All have turned out of the way: they are become unprofitable together: there is none that doth good, there is not so much as one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:13",
      "text": "Their throat is an open sepulchre: with their tongues they have dealt deceitfully. The venom of asps is under their lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:14",
      "text": "Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:15",
      "text": "Their feet swift to shed blood:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:16",
      "text": "Destruction and misery in their ways:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:17",
      "text": "And the way of peace they have not known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:18",
      "text": "There is no fear of God before their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:19",
      "text": "Now we know that what things soever the law speaketh, it speaketh to them that are in the law: that every mouth may be stopped and all the world may be made subject to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:20",
      "text": "Because by the works of the law no flesh shall be justified before him. For by the law is the knowledge of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:21",
      "text": "But now, without the law, the justice of God is made manifest, being witnessed by the law and the prophets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:22",
      "text": "Even the justice of God, by faith of Jesus Christ, unto all, and upon all them that believe in him: for there is no distinction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:23",
      "text": "For all have sinned and do need the glory of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:24",
      "text": "Being justified freely by his grace, through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:25",
      "text": "Whom God hath proposed to be a propitiation, through faith in his blood, to the shewing of his justice, for the remission of former sins,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:26",
      "text": "Through the forbearance of God, for the shewing of his justice in this time: that he himself may be just and the justifier of him who is of the faith of Jesus Christ",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:27",
      "text": "Where is then thy boasting? It is excluded. By what law? Of works? No, but by the law of faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:28",
      "text": "For we account a man to be justified by faith, without the works of the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:29",
      "text": "Is he the God of the Jews only? Is he not also of the Gentiles? yes, of the Gentiles also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:30",
      "text": "For it is one God that justifieth circumcision by faith and uncircumcision through faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:romans.3.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:31",
      "text": "Do we then, destroy the law through faith? God forbid! But we establish the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
